### ðŸŽ¨ 2. `SupportPage.css`

```css
.support-container {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  padding: 30px;
  background: #fff;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.heading {
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: bold;
  margin-bottom: 30px;
}

.support-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: 20px;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .support-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }
}

.card {
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 20px;
  background: #fefefe;
  box-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
}

.red-card {
  border-color: #f44336;
  background-color: #ffe6e6;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 15px;
}

.link {
  color: #007bff;
  text-decoration: underline;
  display: block;
  margin: 10px 0;
}

.button-group {
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.btn {
  padding: 8px 12px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.btn.blue {
  background-color: #007bff;
  color: #fff;
}

.btn.light-blue {
  background-color: #e0f0ff;
  color: #007bff;
}

.note {
  font-size: 14px;
  color: #555;
}

.email-block p {
  margin: 12px 0;
}

.email-block span {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: gray;
}

.red-heading {
  color: #c62828;
}

.phone-number {
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: bold;
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 20px;
}
```

---

### ðŸ§ª How to Use

1. Place both files inside your React app.
2. Import and render `<SupportPage />` in `App.js`.

